  "datePublished": "2026-04-30",
  "description": "A genealogy of rubber-hose realism — a U.S. soft-power aesthetic running from Fleischer's Koko the Clown and Disney's Mickey Mouse to the 4th PSYOP Group's Ghosts in the Machine — that uses cartoon elasticity, infantilization, and consequence-free violence to manage audience affect.",
  "name": "Rubber-Hose Realism: From Koko the Clown and Mickey Mouse to the Aesthetic Toolkit of the U.S. 4th Psychological Operations Group",
